
Usage:
    sfbcep [options] ifile ofile

Synopsis:
    Filter-bank based cepstral analysis of the input signal.

Options:
  -F, --format=s            input signal file format (pcm16)
  -f, --sample-rate=n       signal sample rate for pcm16 input (8000.0 Hz)
  -x, --channel=n           channel number (1)
  -B, --swap                swap sample byte order (don't)
  -I, --input-bufsize=n     input buffer size in kbytes (10000)
  -O, --output-bufsize=n    output buffer size in kbytes (10000)

  -k, --pre-emphasis=f      pre-emphasis coefficient (0.95)
  -l, --length=f            frame length in ms (20.0 ms)
  -d, --shift=f             frame shift in ms (10.0 ms)
  -w, --window=s            weighting window (HAMMING)

  -n, --num-filter=n        number of filters in the filter-bank (24)
  -a, --alpha=f             frequency warping parameter (0.0)
  -m, --mel                 use MEL frequency scale (off)
  -i, --freq-min=n          lower frequency bound (0 Hz)
  -u, --freq-max=n          higher frequency bound (Fs/2)
  -b, --fft-length=n        FFT length (512)

  -p, --num-ceps=n          number of cepstral coefficients (12)
  -r, --lifter=n            liftering value (0)

  -e, --energy              add log-energy (off)
  -s, --scale-energy=f      scale and normalize log-energy (off)

  -Z, --cms                 cepstral mean normalization
  -R, --normalize           variance normalization
  -L, --segment-length=n    segment length in frames for normalization (whole data)
  -D, --delta               add first order derivatives
  -A, --acceleration        add second order derivatives
  -N, --no-static-energy    remove static energy

  -v, --verbose             verbose mode
  -V, --version             print version number and exit
  -h, --help                this help message

